am f weld book  editions published between  and  in english and held by  worldcat member libraries worldwide in  five towns in western massachusetts were flooded to create a huge reservoir fifteenyearold jamieson who lives on a farm with his ironic and strongwilled grandmother watches life unravel for the men and women whose world is about to be obliterated some take refuge in whiskey or denial some give in to despair some preach hypocrisy and some decide to turn a profit on their fellow citizens misfortunesjacket mackerel by moonlight  a novel by william f weld book  editions published between  and  in english and held by  worldcat member libraries worldwide a satire on state politics featuring lawyer terrence mullally  contesting an election for district attorney in boston he is a nobody but wins by following the advice of his spin doctor he delivers the right sound bites sucks up to the right people and sleeps with the right married woman a first novel by a former governor of massachusetts big ugly  a novel by william f weld book  editions published between  and  in english and held by  worldcat member libraries worldwide a satire on washington politics featuring the art of squeezing the maximum amount of cash from lobbyists the hero is a freshman senator who is learning the ropes by a former massachusetts governor author of mackerel by moonlight handbook on the antidrug abuse act of  book  editions published in  in english and held by  worldcat member libraries worldwide asset forfeiture  compilation of civil statutes by james v katz  in english and held by  worldcat member libraries worldwide meet the press visual  editions published in  in english and held by  worldcat member libraries worldwide on this edition of meet the press william weld discusses the blocking of his ambassadorial nomination by jesse helms susan and william mcmillan discuss paula jones case against president clinton congressman dan burton discusses the fundraising investigation into vice p